Returns a raw pointer to the array's buffer.

This is equivalent to casting `self` to `*const T`, but more type-safe.

# Examples

```rust
#![feature(array_ptr_get)]
use std::ptr;

let arr: *const [i8; 3] = ptr::null();
assert_eq!(arr.as_ptr(), ptr::null());
```
